The paper deals with the combinatorial and geometric properties of arrangements of pseudocircles, which are objects studied in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial arguments and graph theory, which suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as likely sub-categories. The study of arrangements and their properties involves data structures and algorithms, which could place the paper in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses drawing algorithms and techniques, which could make cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category.
